VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'photo inside of the folder. And I\'m just going to paste that prompt in and I\'m going to say go. So now we can see Claude is getting to work. It was able to find the image. I didn\'t even give it a good name and it\'s going to pull in the EVO precision lens cleaner and the'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one line pitch. A pocket size precision spray that strips smudges, oils and dust from eyeglasses, camera lenses and screens without streaking or scratching. That\'s pretty solid. So then it goes ahead and it actually generates this brand promise which is basically like'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'why this product is better than all the other ones. And then it goes ahead and just gives like five proof points about why this product is awesome. It extracts all of the brand colors like the electric sky blue. It figures out what the brand mood is. So like clean, technical, modern, masculine, right? So'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it kind of just like references what this bottle looks like. And then it basically just decided who might want to actually buy this product. Practical, tech forward, 25 to 45 year old glasses wearers, remote workers. Does this sound familiar? So now we have the first piece'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but it gets so much better because Claude code can actually do the part that most people don\'t want to do which is research. And this part is super important because this is actually what decides whether or not you can sell a product. So this prompt is going to use'

